caption.p: Effect of ULV of selected oils (10 mL/L) that were sprayed for 15 s on oviposition substrate, on the cumulative number of eggs that were laid at the 5, 10 and 15th days after treatment by female fruit moths ( A. lineatella) in the choice test. The different symbols, (*,+), above treatment (dark blue) and control (green) bars, indicate pair wise significant differences ( P < 0.05, t-tests).
